{
  "stem": "2581.6",
  "chunk_idx": 4,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 10.0,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "So my father take care of the family, and he sent us on vacations.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "A few miles from our hometown.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And one time we went from the school on a trip to Warsaw.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "That was something spend-thrift.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "I mean very, spend-thrift, yes, because it was expensive.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And not many children would-- I don't remember exactly the details of what happened there.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "Because the war broke out, I was 13.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "So I could have been 10 at the time.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "In our time, there were two elementary schools.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "There was one, a dilapidated building for the Jewish children.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "As I said before, there were 50 % Jewish people in our town.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And another building, a brand new brick building, four-story building for the gentile children.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Now we were very crowded, so they give us one floor in that brick building, but it was the top floor.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And God forbid if anyone of us was stuck during recess and we were late, going up to our fourth room.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And if they caught us on the steps, they would beat us.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "They would fight with us, the Polish boys, you know.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "But that's what it was.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "That was the way of life.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "Before you went to the cheder or to the [NON-ENGLISH] that I later went to, we had that in the evening.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "It was the public school was in the morning till 2:00 and 5:00 to 8:00 we had the Jewish school, the cheder.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "We would never walk alone.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "When we walked out, there would be 10 of us.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "And even so, we wouldn't fight them.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "Because all they-- shortly before the war, it was such a situation that a Polish person could say that we called him a Polish pig, and the parents would be responsible.",
      "word_count": 31
    }
  ],
